Geri Horner, 49, and her husband Christian Horner, 48, travelled to Glastonbury in style as they flew to watch Paul McCartney in a helicopter from their country home.The couple shared details of their date night on social media, posting snaps from take-off to watching Paul's highly anticipated headline set.In true Geri style, she attended the festival in her trademark all-white outfit, complete with a high-neck top, trousers, raincoat and biker boots.F1 Principal Christian looked casual in blue jeans, a navy jumper and brown lace-up boots.In a selfie shared to Geri’s Instagram, the couple posed in front of the helicopter and she wrote: “Date night to see a legend @PaulMcCartney.”